3:9728.name: Configuration=Medium, Elevation=flat
3:9728.description: Collapsing top app bars can be used for longer titles, to house imagery, or to provide a stronger presence to the top app bar.

3:5916.name: Style=Standard, State=Enabled
3:5916.description:
Standard Icon buttons are low-emphasis buttons.
They are used for the lowest priority actions, especially when presenting multiple options.

Icon buttons can be placed on a variety of backgrounds. Until the button is interacted with, its container isn’t visible.

3:5780.name: Style=Outlined
3:5780.description: Cards are versatile containers, holding anything from images to headlines, supporting text, buttons, lists, and other components.

3:5743.name: State=Enabled
3:5743.description: Cards are versatile containers, holding anything from images to headlines, supporting text, buttons, lists, and other components.

3:6321.name: Configuration=Icon & label, Segments=3
3:6321.description: 3 segment Next navigation bar with icon & label

3:9725.name: Top app bar
3:9725.description: Use a top app bar to provide content and actions related to a current screen, such as navigation, screen headlines, and actions.

3:5896.name: Icon button
3:5896.description:
Icon buttons display actions in a compact layout. Icon buttons can represent opening actions such as opening an overflow menu or search, or represent binary actions that can be toggled on and off, such as favorite or bookmark.

Icon buttons can be grouped together or they can stand alone.

3:5779.name: Horizontal card
3:5779.description: Cards are used to display content and actions on a single topic. They should be easy to scan for relevant and actionable information. Cards can be displayed together in a grid, vertical list, or carousel.

3:6320.name: Navigation bar
3:6320.description:
Navigation bars (nav bars) provide access to three to five destinations.

The nav bar is positioned at the bottom of screens for convenient access. Each destination is represented by an icon and optional text label.
When a navigation bar icon is tapped or focused, the user is taken to the navigation destination associated with that icon. 

Use on mobile or tablet only.

🛠 Additional options 
Segments - can be edited by selecting individual segments and  selecting states, labels, and badges from the variant properties.
